NEW DELHI, Nov. 10 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Admiral R. Hari Kumar will be the next chief of the Indian Navy, the Indian government said late on Tuesday. Presently the Flag Officer Commanding-in-Chief of the Western Naval Command, he will take charge with effect from Nov. 30. The present Chief of the Naval Staff Admiral Karambir Singh retires from service on the same day. Kumar was commissioned into the Indian Navy in January 1983. Enditem